{"title_page": "Peter Horby", "text_new": "'''Peter Horby''' is a British epidemiologist, and a Professor of Emerging Infectious Diseases and Global Health at the University of Oxford. He is the Chair of the UK government's New and Emerging Respiratory Virus Threats Advisory Group (NERVTAG). Peter is the former, and founding Director of the Oxford University Clinical Research Unit in Hanoi, Vietnam. Established in early 2006, the unit conducts research on infectious diseases which crosses the disciplines of basic science, medical science and public health. In 2014 he established the Epidemic diseases Research Group Oxford (ERGO). Ergo is involved in a number of international projects including the European Commission funded PREPARE and ALERRT projects, the International Severe Acute Respiratory and Emerging Infection Consortium (ISARIC) and the UK Public Health Rapid Support Team (UK-PHRST). In June 2016, Peter became Chair of ISARIC, taking over from outgoing Chair Abdullah Brooks. \n\n\n\nPeter specialises in the design of control programmes against infectious diseases.\n\nHorby is one of the 23 attendees of the Scientific Advisory Group for Emergencies (SAGE) <ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite news |last1=Sample |first1=Ian |title=Who's who on secret scientific group advising UK government? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/24/coronavirus-whos-who-on-secret-scientific-group-advising-uk-government-sage |accessdate=24 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=24 April 2020}}</ref> He is the chair of the [[New and Emerging Respiratory Virus Threats Advisory Group]] (NERVTAG).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/new-and-emerging-respiratory-virus-threats-advisory-group|title=New and Emerging Respiratory Virus Threats Advisory Group|website=gov.uk|language=en|access-date=24 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"The Guardian\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ho